snippet.textDisplay: years ago i once auditioned for toy commercial that'd be on cartoon network. I was probably one of the oldest kids there so I was treating it like it was some dumb kid thing.  I went into the auditioning room with the other kids and there was a guy and his female assistant holding a clipboard. the room was lit by a single softbox light that was by his desk. the first thing he said was anyone that doesn't remember their lines get out now.  And in my head im like this guy is serious he didnt smile make jokes or anything and would tell kids to go before they even finished their script.  it would of been no big deal to me but considering most of the kids were around 12 years old and younger i was like WTF.  Everytime i remember what happened it makes me laugh. i feel like it would be a funny skit being in my shoes cus i was not expecting anything like that at all.
